provenance_notes: A missal of unknown origin, almost certainly used in South-West Finland at the end of the Middle Ages. This attribution is based on the patterns of its sixteenth-century reuse as cover material for tax records. The earliest association to tax records is to tithe accounts from Paimio (Swe. Pemar). It is very likely that the book belonged to the parish church of Paimio, or possibly that of the close by parishes Piikkiö or Sauvo.
